          <td bgcolor="" valign="top" width="1"><img src="/lotr/gfx/trans_header1.gif" width="0" height="2" vspace="0" hspace="0" border="0"></td>
          <td bgcolor="" valign="top"><!-- #BeginEditable "Body" --> 
            <table width=100% border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0>
<tr><td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_01.gif" width=6 height=6></td><td width=100% background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_02.gif"></td>
<td width=1><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_03.gif" width=6 height=6></td></tr>
<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_04.gif"><img src="/lotr/gfx/mom/clear.gif" height=35 width=1></td>
<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/swccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Star Wars TCG</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> The Power of the Signet<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.37)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=3958'>Jeremy "Arkan" McKean</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=3958&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> July 21, 2002</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> Growing tired of seeing all the superfellowship/urukhai decks, I decided to look for something that could overpower the deck type.  Obviously, I had quite a task in front of me.<br>
A deck built around discarding cards often meant you had little to actually fight your opponent, while ally heavy decks can still be hurt at site 7 if they dont watch themselves (&quot;Gee, I can exert Galadriel to play a forest at site 7 instead.. er, wait, thats skip archery. :)&quot;), or by Tower Assassins and Our List of Allies Grows Thin.  Nazgul have a lot of trouble actually fighting the super fellowship, but could possibly get away with twilight nazgul burden madness.  All hobbits have always had a chance... against anything but uruks.<br>
There are many possibilities, but one major problem I came across was the fact that some of the better fellowship concepts couldn&#39;t work well with the better shadow concepts. So I instead looked at something else for the fellowship side: the Signet. All three signets have different cards supporting them, and the three different versions of each companion are completely different in ability.<br>
So, now that the long boring introduction is past, lets actually look at each signet. ;)<br>
<br>
FRODO:<br>
Frodo, Son of Drogo - <br>
Fellowship: Exert a companion with the Frodo signet to heal Frodo.<br>
As everyone knows (and screams), Son of Drogo is one of the absolute most worthless cards in the game. But lets keep looking.<br>
<br>
Dear Friends - <br>
Fellowship: Exert a companion to place a fellowship card from your discard pile beneath your draw deck (or two cards if that companion has the Frodo signet).<br>
Not a bad card, I suppose, but Fireworks does it without the exert and always gets two cards, in addition to the option of pulling Gandalf cards back.<br>
<br>
Frodo&#39;s Pipe -<br>
Fellowship: Discard a pipeweed possession and spot X pipes to heal a companion with the Frodo signet X times.<br>
Gah!!! This card is disturbing. Greenleaf and Heir to the White City with a bow can fire much more often, knowing they can be healed later.<br>
<br>
Clearly, a Frodo Signet deck seems to work best around pipeweed, as you can burn the weed every turn to your archer factory. :)  Dear Friends can work if you need the extra deck retrieval, I suppose.  But don&#39;t bother with Son of Drogo, unless you don&#39;t care about the extra twilight from playing things on Frodo, in which case he&#39;s a great sponge to exert for Dear Friends.<br>
<br>
Companions with the Frodo Signet:<br>
Frodo, Son of Drogo<br>
Aragorn, Heir to the White City<br>
Arwen, Elven Rider<br>
Boromir, Son of Denethor<br>
Gandalf, Friend to the Shirefolk<br>
Gimli, Dwarf of the Mountain-Race<br>
Legolas, Greenleaf<br>
Merry, Friend to Sam<br>
Pippen, Friend to Frodo<br>
Sam, Faithful Companion<br>
<br>
Heir to the White City and Greenleaf are the important ones here, followed closely by Friend to Sam and Son of Denethor, as they have great abilities that require them to exert (Well, Aragorn needs his bow, but aside from that...)<br>
<br>
<br>
GANDALF:<br>
Gandalf, The Grey Wizard - <br>
Fellowship: Exert Gandalf to play a companion with the Gandalf Signet. That Companion&#39;s Twilight cost is -2.<br>
His ability is a bit iffy, but he is Gandalf Signet, I suppose...<br>
<br>
Gandalf&#39;s Wisdom - <br>
The twilight cost of each possession or artifact played on Gandalf or a character who has the Gandalf Signet is -1.<br>
I&#39;m a bit surprised no one uses this. I prefer Jarnsmid in some cases, but Gandalf having a sword, staff, and ring for a total cost of 2 twilight just rocks.  It isn&#39;t limited to just combat possessions either, so pipes, cloaks, horses, etc are affected too. :)<br>
<br>
Trust Me as You Once Did -<br>
Skirmish: Exert Gandalf to make a companion strength +1 for each companion with the Gandalf signet you can spot (limit +3)<br>
Ok, so Gandalf, with his vitality of 6, can exert to make someone strength +3? Yes please. :)  This is clearly the card that would make anyone play all Gandalf signet.<br>
<br>
Overall, Gandalf Signet is for fighting. TMaYOD is a condition that you can use to pump your guys at any time (and even use Strength of Spirit to do it some more), while Gandalf&#39;s Wisdom will get out those needed weapons at a reduced twilight cost. As with Son of Drogo, I wouldn&#39;t suggest building around using The Grey Wizard&#39;s ability, but he and Old Bilbo&#39;s Heir guarantees at least a +2 from TMaYOD.<br>
<br>
Companions with the Gandalf Signet:<br>
Frodo, Old Bilbo&#39;s Heir<br>
Aragorn, Ranger of the North<br>
Arwen, Lady Undomiel<br>
Boromir, Defender of Minas Tirith<br>
Gandalf, The Grey Wizard<br>
Gimli, Son of Gloin<br>
Legolas, Prince of Mirkwood<br>
Merry, Horticulturalist<br>
Pippin, Hobbit of Some Intelligence<br>
Sam, Proper Poet<br>
<br>
Wow, both exert to be defender +1&#39;s are Gandalf signet. Weird, ne? Having both OBH and Horticulturalist can be interesting, as Gandalf adds even more power to the already strong Hobbit deck. <br>
<br>
<br>
ARAGORN:<br>
Aragorn, King in Exile - <br>
At the start of each of your turns, you may heal another companion with the Aragorn signet.<br>
If that&#39;s not an invitation for the super fellowship to take advantage of, I don&#39;t know what is.  With Aragorn healing Son of Thranduil, Daughter of Elrond, even The Grey Pilgrim and Reluctant Adventurer, its easy to understand why.<br>
<br>
No Mere Ranger -<br>
Skirmish: Exert Aragorn to make another companion strength +2 (or +3 if that companion has the Aragorn signet).<br>
Not bad, I suppose, but super fellowships arent exactly known for playing pump events. The fact that it is an event and not a condition like TMaYOD makes it exponentially less useful.<br>
<br>
Voice of Rauros -<br>
Maneuver: Exert Aragorn to make each companion with the Aragorn signet damage +1 until the regroup phase.<br>
Meep. This utterly slays Isengard Orcs, and can even knock off those pesky fierce Uruk-hai if your opponent can&#39;t prevent the wounds. It can also make cards like His Cruelty and Malice useless.<br>
<br>
Overall, the Aragorn signet is the most popular to build around, and with good reason. Of course, that reason has nothing to do with any of the support cards for it as much as it does just KiE.<br>
<br>
Companions with the Aragorn signet:<br>
Frodo, Reluctant Adventurer<br>
Aragorn, King in Exile<br>
Arwen, Daughter of Elrond<br>
Boromir, Lord of Gondor<br>
Gandalf, the Grey Pilgrim<br>
Gimli, Dwarf of Erebor<br>
Legolas, Son of Thranduil<br>
Merry, From O&#39;er the Brandywine<br>
Pippin, Mr. Took<br>
Sam, Son of Hamfast<br>
<br>
DoE, LoG, and tGP seem to be the big ones here, as is SoT if he&#39;s using The Splendor of their Banners. Sam is also a nice one, just because he can heal from Aragorn, and then exert to remove a burden. EVERY TURN. Blade Tip Frodo all you want. ;) Of course, Gates of the Dead City gets around that.<br>
<br>
In conlusion, all of the signets have a special attachment to them that can empower an already popular decktype.  I hope that this article has helped to open a new look on how the fellowship side can work together, as opposed to being a mass of strongarms trying to fight off the opponent&#39;s shadow. <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?id=3877&view=1'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
